{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_Mw6bbfA7mG7RBxCgPaVvDgzv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_tables\n3\toutput:\n4\t  tables: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, read_sources]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tTurn the holistic table list into a DETAILED, source-grounded data model. `query`, `read_sources`\n11\t(the build brief), and `plan_app` (`plan_app.tables` is the high-level list) are in scope. This is\n12\tstill a THINKING step — no writers here. For every table produce its full `schema` AND the actual\n13\t`rows` read from the material, so the implement step can seed data at creation. Do NOT invent rows: use\n14\tonly values the source states (identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, attribution). If\n15\tthe source has no rows for a table, drop that table — a created-but-empty table is the #1 failure.\n16\t\n17\tEvery table schema needs a `title`, a `description`, and `columns` where each column has a\n18\t`description` and exactly one uuid primary key. Keys in each row object MUST match the column names.\n19\tEmit one statement:\n20\t\n21\t```typescript\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n23\t  tables: [\n24\t    {\n25\t      name: '<source-derived table name>',\n26\t      schema: {\n27\t        title: '<Title>',\n28\t        description: '<what this table stores>',\n29\t        columns: {\n30\t          id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' },\n31\t          // …one column per field the record carries, each with a real description.\n32\t        },\n33\t      },\n34\t      // One object per record READ FROM THE MATERIAL. Never carry over an example value.\n35\t      rows: [ /* { id: '…', …source-derived fields } */ ],\n36\t    },\n37\t  ],\n38\t});\n39\t```\n40\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tPb0UsB1toyLruNLs583FlmL","session_id":"9c7a9dc1-bb8c-4315-b194-e357aac0f2c7","uuid":"16ff1e60-3707-4382-9f30-f3cc240780c7","timestamp":"2026-07-16T18:28:31.014Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace endpoint build failure"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_opuQzXJS11V0YL1FKbWbxcmT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\texport const name = 'park-fees-by-type';\n2\texport const description = 'Return all park fees grouped by a single fee_type (entry_permit, vehicle_entry, camping, crater_service, walking_safari, ranger) — used for the category-filtered view on the Park Fee Reference page.';\n3\t\n4\texport interface Input {\n5\t  feeType: string; // URL path param: one of entry_permit, vehicle_entry, camping, crater_service, walking_safari, ranger\n6\t}\n7\t\n8\texport interface ParkFeeItem {\n9\t  id: string;\n10\t  fee_type: string;\n11\t  subcategory: string;\n12\t  citizen_category: string | null;\n13\t  age_group: string | null;\n14\t  amount_usd: number | null;\n15\t  amount_tzs: number | null;\n16\t  vat_note: string | null;\n17\t  validity_note: string | null;\n18\t  source_note: string | null;\n19\t}\n20\t\n21\texport interface Output {\n22\t  items: ParkFeeItem[];\n23\t  feeType: string;\n24\t  count: number;\n25\t}\n26\t\n27\texport default async function handler(input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\n28\t  // Query all park_fees rows, then filter by fee_type matching the URL param\n29\t  const allRows: ParkFeeItem[] = await ctx.db.query('park_fees');\n30\t  const feeType = input.feeType;\n31\t  const items = allRows.filter((row: ParkFeeItem) => row.fee_type === feeType);\n32\t  return { items, feeType, count: items.length };\n33\t}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tPb0UsB1toyLruNLs583FlmL","session_id":"9c7a9dc1-bb8c-4315-b194-e357aac0f2c7","uuid":"3c6f6b6a-6e03-4c77-87d5-b3f90cd2dbb9","timestamp":"2026-07-16T18:28:31.015Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace endpoint build failure"}
