{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_gaehtAs5bmdLp0YiLR06ZaQp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_tables\n3\toutput:\n4\t  tables: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, read_sources]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tTurn the holistic table list into a DETAILED, source-grounded data model. `query`, `read_sources`\n11\t(the build brief), and `plan_app` (`plan_app.tables` is the high-level list) are in scope. This is\n12\tstill a THINKING step — no writers here. For every table produce its full `schema` AND the actual\n13\t`rows` read from the material, so the implement step can seed data at creation. Do NOT invent rows: use\n14\tonly values the source states (identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, attribution). If\n15\tthe source has no rows for a table, drop that table — a created-but-empty table is the #1 failure.\n16\t\n17\tEvery table schema needs a `title`, a `description`, and `columns` where each column has a\n18\t`description` and exactly one uuid primary key. Keys in each row object MUST match the column names.\n19\tEmit one statement:\n20\t\n21\t```typescript\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n23\t  tables: [\n24\t    {\n25\t      name: '<source-derived table name>',\n26\t      schema: {\n27\t        title: '<Title>',\n28\t        description: '<what this table stores>',\n29\t        columns: {\n30\t          id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' },\n31\t          // …one column per field the record carries, each with a real description.\n32\t        },\n33\t      },\n34\t      // One object per record READ FROM THE MATERIAL. Never carry over an example value.\n35\t      rows: [ /* { id: '…', …source-derived fields } */ ],\n36\t    },\n37\t  ],\n38\t});\n39\t```\n40\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7a9dc1-bb8c-4315-b194-e357aac0f2c7","uuid":"515ac026-8916-47e2-a47f-fa92bc06492f","timestamp":"2026-07-16T18:32:20.591Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/03-plan_tables.md","content":"---\nid: plan_tables\noutput:\n  tables: array\ndependsOn: [plan_app, read_sources]\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nTurn the holistic table list into a DETAILED, source-grounded data model. `query`, `read_sources`\n(the build brief), and `plan_app` (`plan_app.tables` is the high-level list) are in scope. This is\nstill a THINKING step — no writers here. For every table produce its full `schema` AND the actual\n`rows` read from the material, so the implement step can seed data at creation. Do NOT invent rows: use\nonly values the source states (identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, attribution). If\nthe source has no rows for a table, drop that table — a created-but-empty table is the #1 failure.\n\nEvery table schema needs a `title`, a `description`, and `columns` where each column has a\n`description` and exactly one uuid primary key. Keys in each row object MUST match the column names.\nEmit one statement:\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  tables: [\n    {\n      name: '<source-derived table name>',\n      schema: {\n        title: '<Title>',\n        description: '<what this table stores>',\n        columns: {\n          id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' },\n          // …one column per field the record carries, each with a real description.\n        },\n      },\n      // One object per record READ FROM THE MATERIAL. Never carry over an example value.\n      rows: [ /* { id: '…', …source-derived fields } */ ],\n    },\n  ],\n});\n```\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}}}
