{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_LS6ml0l1i6jcbK73H1opiDFQ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_pages\n3\toutput:\n4\t  pages: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints, plan_components]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tPlan the MULTIPLE pages of the app, each wired to the real endpoints and the reusable components.\n11\t`query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.pages`), `plan_endpoints` (`plan_endpoints.endpoints` — each is\n12\t`{ name, route, purpose, tables }`), and `plan_components` (`plan_components.components`) are in scope.\n13\tThis is a THINKING step — no writers. **Every endpoint a page lists must be an existing\n14\t`plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`, copied VERBATIM — never invent a name or transform one.** Plan an\n15\t`index` home PLUS the additional views the material calls for (a list, a detail `items/[id]`, a\n16\tdashboard) — a single page is not enough. For each page, list the endpoint `name`s it reads and the\n17\tcomponents it renders, so the implement step wires real data through shared UI. Emit one statement:\n18\t\n19\t```typescript\n20\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n21\t  pages: [\n22\t    {\n23\t      route: 'index',\n24\t      purpose: '<what this page shows>',\n25\t      // endpoint NAMES, each copied verbatim from plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name:\n26\t      endpoints: [ '<endpoint name>' ],\n27\t      // component names (from plan_components) this page renders:\n28\t      components: [ '<ComponentName>' ],\n29\t    },\n30\t  ],\n31\t});\n32\t```\n33\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7a9dc1-bb8c-4315-b194-e357aac0f2c7","uuid":"d38529f3-5899-4513-8e5a-b12ed3889977","timestamp":"2026-07-16T18:33:03.764Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/09-plan_pages.md","content":"---\nid: plan_pages\noutput:\n  pages: array\ndependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints, plan_components]\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nPlan the MULTIPLE pages of the app, each wired to the real endpoints and the reusable components.\n`query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.pages`), `plan_endpoints` (`plan_endpoints.endpoints` — each is\n`{ name, route, purpose, tables }`), and `plan_components` (`plan_components.components`) are in scope.\nThis is a THINKING step — no writers. **Every endpoint a page lists must be an existing\n`plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`, copied VERBATIM — never invent a name or transform one.** Plan an\n`index` home PLUS the additional views the material calls for (a list, a detail `items/[id]`, a\ndashboard) — a single page is not enough. For each page, list the endpoint `name`s it reads and the\ncomponents it renders, so the implement step wires real data through shared UI. Emit one statement:\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  pages: [\n    {\n      route: 'index',\n      purpose: '<what this page shows>',\n      // endpoint NAMES, each copied verbatim from plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name:\n      endpoints: [ '<endpoint name>' ],\n      // component names (from plan_components) this page renders:\n      components: [ '<ComponentName>' ],\n    },\n  ],\n});\n```\n","numLines":33,"startLine":1,"totalLines":33}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_gTH7y3s0iQLsdFWmD7DPmhp7","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_pages\n3\toutput:\n4\t  route: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [plan_pages, plan_endpoints, plan_components, implement_components]\n7\tforEach: plan_pages.pages\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE React page into the LIVE project's `pages/`. Your page is in `item` =\n13\t{ route, purpose, endpoints, components } (`index` is the home; `items/[id]` is a dynamic route).\n14\t`plan_endpoints.endpoints` and `plan_components.components` are in scope. Write the FULL `.tsx` source\n15\tinline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern (real line breaks).\n16\t\n17\tWiring rules — the app fails to compile if you break them:\n18\t- Import data hooks ONLY from `@app/runtime` (`useApi`/`useApiMutation`/`apiCall`/`Link`/`useParams`) —\n19\t  never `fetch` a raw URL, and NEVER import `react-router`, `@radix-ui/*`, `@agent-chat/react`, or a\n20\t  relative `use-api`; none exist in a generated project.\n21\t- Read data by passing an endpoint `name` to `useApi` — the exact stable id the endpoint exported. Use\n22\t  ONLY names listed for this page in `item.endpoints` (each is a real `plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`);\n23\t  never invent or transform a name. Every read endpoint returns `{ items: [...] }`, so read `data.items`.\n24\t- IMPORT the reusable components you planned, by relative path from `pages/` to `components/`: a\n25\t  top-level page uses `../components/<Name>`, a page one directory deep uses `../../components/<Name>`.\n26\t- STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`,\n27\t  `border-border`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color.\n28\t\n29\t`writeProjectPage` validates the page has a default export and parses, returning `{ ok, error? }`;\n30\trewrite and retry if `w.ok` is false. Emit one statement:\n31\t\n32\t```typescript\n33\tconst pg = item;\n34\tconst depth = String(pg.route).split('/').length; // 'index' → 1, 'items/[id]' → 2\n35\tconst up = '../'.repeat(depth);                    // '../' to reach the project root from this page\n36\tconst ep = (Array.isArray(pg.endpoints) && pg.endpoints[0]) ? pg.endpoints[0]\n37\t  : (plan_endpoints.endpoints[0] ? plan_endpoints.endpoints[0].name : 'items-list');\n38\tconst comp = (Array.isArray(pg.components) && pg.components[0]) ? pg.components[0]\n39\t  : (plan_components.components[0] ? plan_components.components[0].name : null);\n40\tconst src = [\n41\t  \"import { useApi } from '@app/runtime';\",\n42\t  comp ? (\"import \" + comp + \" from '\" + up + \"components/\" + comp + \"';\") : \"\",\n43\t  \"\",\n44\t  \"export default function Page() {\",\n45\t  \"  const { data, isLoading, error } = useApi<{ items: { id: string; title?: string }[] }>('\" + ep + \"');\",\n46\t  \"  if (isLoading) return <p className=\\\"p-4 text-muted\\\">Loading…</p>;\",\n47\t  \"  if (error) return <p className=\\\"p-4 text-destructive\\\">Could not load data.</p>;\",\n48\t  \"  return (\",\n49\t  \"    <main className=\\\"space-y-2 p-4\\\">\",\n50\t  \"      {(data?.items ?? []).map((it) => (\",\n51\t  comp ? (\"        <\" + comp + \" key={it.id} title={it.title ?? it.id} />\") : \"        <div key={it.id} className=\\\"text-foreground\\\">{it.title ?? it.id}</div>\",\n52\t  \"      ))}\",\n53\t  \"    </main>\",\n54\t  \"  );\",\n55\t  \"}\",\n56\t].filter((line) => line !== \"\").join(\"\\n\");\n57\tconst w = writeProjectPage(pg.route, src);\n58\tcurrentTask.resolve({ route: pg.route, ok: w.ok });\n59\t```\n60\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7a9dc1-bb8c-4315-b194-e357aac0f2c7","uuid":"32381498-20b2-4627-a6de-6a9eee01ae73","timestamp":"2026-07-16T18:33:03.764Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/10-implement_pages.md","content":"---\nid: implement_pages\noutput:\n  route: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [plan_pages, plan_endpoints, plan_components, implement_components]\nforEach: plan_pages.pages\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nWrite ONE React page into the LIVE project's `pages/`. Your page is in `item` =\n{ route, purpose, endpoints, components } (`index` is the home; `items/[id]` is a dynamic route).\n`plan_endpoints.endpoints` and `plan_components.components` are in scope. Write the FULL `.tsx` source\ninline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern (real line breaks).\n\nWiring rules — the app fails to compile if you break them:\n- Import data hooks ONLY from `@app/runtime` (`useApi`/`useApiMutation`/`apiCall`/`Link`/`useParams`) —\n  never `fetch` a raw URL, and NEVER import `react-router`, `@radix-ui/*`, `@agent-chat/react`, or a\n  relative `use-api`; none exist in a generated project.\n- Read data by passing an endpoint `name` to `useApi` — the exact stable id the endpoint exported. Use\n  ONLY names listed for this page in `item.endpoints` (each is a real `plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`);\n  never invent or transform a name. Every read endpoint returns `{ items: [...] }`, so read `data.items`.\n- IMPORT the reusable components you planned, by relative path from `pages/` to `components/`: a\n  top-level page uses `../components/<Name>`, a page one directory deep uses `../../components/<Name>`.\n- STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`,\n  `border-border`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color.\n\n`writeProjectPage` validates the page has a default export and parses, returning `{ ok, error? }`;\nrewrite and retry if `w.ok` is false. Emit one statement:\n\n```typescript\nconst pg = item;\nconst depth = String(pg.route).split('/').length; // 'index' → 1, 'items/[id]' → 2\nconst up = '../'.repeat(depth);                    // '../' to reach the project root from this page\nconst ep = (Array.isArray(pg.endpoints) && pg.endpoints[0]) ? pg.endpoints[0]\n  : (plan_endpoints.endpoints[0] ? plan_endpoints.endpoints[0].name : 'items-list');\nconst comp = (Array.isArray(pg.components) && pg.components[0]) ? pg.components[0]\n  : (plan_components.components[0] ? plan_components.components[0].name : null);\nconst src = [\n  \"import { useApi } from '@app/runtime';\",\n  comp ? (\"import \" + comp + \" from '\" + up + \"components/\" + comp + \"';\") : \"\",\n  \"\",\n  \"export default function Page() {\",\n  \"  const { data, isLoading, error } = useApi<{ items: { id: string; title?: string }[] }>('\" + ep + \"');\",\n  \"  if (isLoading) return <p className=\\\"p-4 text-muted\\\">Loading…</p>;\",\n  \"  if (error) return <p className=\\\"p-4 text-destructive\\\">Could not load data.</p>;\",\n  \"  return (\",\n  \"    <main className=\\\"space-y-2 p-4\\\">\",\n  \"      {(data?.items ?? []).map((it) => (\",\n  comp ? (\"        <\" + comp + \" key={it.id} title={it.title ?? it.id} />\") : \"        <div key={it.id} className=\\\"text-foreground\\\">{it.title ?? it.id}</div>\",\n  \"      ))}\",\n  \"    </main>\",\n  \"  );\",\n  \"}\",\n].filter((line) => line !== \"\").join(\"\\n\");\nconst w = writeProjectPage(pg.route, src);\ncurrentTask.resolve({ route: pg.route, ok: w.ok });\n```\n","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":60}}}
