servation-area-tariffs.pdf) is the official tariff schedule for the Ngorongoro Conservation Area. It details entry permits by age group and residency status, conservation tariffs, ranger fees, and vehicle entry charges. The voice memo reveals an extra ~5,000 TZS ranger tip expectation not mentioned in the official tariff document — a gap the specialist should clarify.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"findings\\\\\\\":[\\\\\\\"Entry permit for non-East African citizens aged 16+: listed in the tariff PDF (exact USD amount extracted from document). Children 5–16 and under 5 have separate rates (ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf).\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"The PDF includes conservation tariffs, ranger rates, and vehicle entry fees — structured as official government-published rates (ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf).\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"The voice memo reports an unexpected ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash requested at the gate, separate from all official fees listed in the PDF — Vasilis was not told about this beforehand and needs to verify with Richard (specialistFacts).\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"The official tariff PDF is the authoritative source for park fees. The specialist should help users understand which fees apply to their group composition and clarify whether the gate ranger tip is a customary practice outside official tariffs or a one-off situation. The discrepancy between official rates and the unexpected tip is a key advisory point.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"sources\\\\\\\":[]}\\\"\\nInputs from upstream tasks (available as variables):\\n- design: {\\\"slug\\\":\\\"ngorongoro-fees\\\",\\\"goal\\\":\\\"Advise on official Ngorongoro entry permits, conservation fees, ranger rates, vehicle charges, park regulations, and the customary ranger tip not covered by official tariffs.\\\",\\\"actionId\\\":\\\"answer\\\",\\\"fields\\\":[{\\\"domain\\\":\\\"ngorongoro\\\",\\\"field\\\":\\\"tariffs\\\",\\\"aspects\\\":[\\\"entry-permits\\\",\\\"conservation-fees\\\",\\\"ranger-rates